            <mixed-citation publication-type="other">Cf. Dancy's (1993, 112, 125) discussion of the relationship between narrative what he calls “shape,” which is the total picture of salience-relations in a given view of a situation. Explaining context-dependence through the selectivity involved in narrative seems to me to be more helpful than describing situations as having shape, especially since situations can apparently have more than one shape at the same time.</mixed-citation>
